WEBVTT



00:00:00.576 --> 00:00:09.920
Hello friends, I'm Rick Warren and welcome to Spurgeon's Sermons. This is the official podcast brought to you by Premier and Spurgeon's College.

00:00:09.920 --> 00:00:19.968
You know the teachings of Charles Spurgeon have had a personal impact on my life in a profound way and I'm confident they'll do the same for you. So get ready to be challenged.

00:00:19.488 --> 00:00:28.224
be challenged, equipped, and guided by Charles Spurgeon, who is universally regarded as the greatest English preacher in the history of the Church.

00:00:29.600 --> 00:00:31.232
Silver sockets

00:00:31.264 --> 00:00:33.888
or redemption, the foundation.

00:00:34.112 --> 00:00:36.224
A sermon by Charles Spurgeon.

00:00:36.576 --> 00:00:37.728
Part one.

00:00:38.752 --> 00:00:45.472
And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, When thou takest the sum of the children of Israel after their number,

00:00:45.824 --> 00:00:52.352
Then shall they give every man a ransom for his soul unto the Lord, when thou numberest them.

00:00:52.768 --> 00:00:55.488
That there be no plague among them.

00:00:55.488 --> 00:00:57.248
When there are numbers, them.

00:00:57.664 --> 00:01:02.784
This they shall give, every one that passeth among them that are numbered.

00:01:02.560 --> 00:01:03.968
Half a shekel,

00:01:04.160 --> 00:01:06.560
After the shekel of the sanctuary,

00:01:06.720 --> 00:01:09.504
A shekel is twenty geras.

00:01:10.336 --> 00:01:13.696
And half shekel shall be the offering of the Lord.

00:01:13.888 --> 00:01:17.536
Everyone that passeth among them that are numbered

00:01:17.248 --> 00:01:19.872
From 20 years old and above,

00:01:19.872 --> 00:01:22.464
Shall give an offering unto the Lord.

00:01:22.912 --> 00:01:25.504
The rich shall not give more,

00:01:25.728 --> 00:01:29.728
And the poor shall not give less than half a shekel.

00:01:29.760 --> 00:01:33.600
When they give an offering unto the Lord, to make an atonement,

00:01:33.536 --> 00:01:34.944
For your souls

00:01:35.840 --> 00:01:40.192
And thou shalt take the atonement money of the children of Israel,

00:01:40.032 --> 00:01:44.448
And shall appoint it for the service of the tabernacle of the congregation.

00:01:45.120 --> 00:01:49.888
That it may be a memorial unto the children of Israel before the Lord.

00:01:49.664 --> 00:01:53.024
To make an atonement for your souls.

00:01:53.664 --> 00:01:55.968
Exodus chapter 30

00:01:55.840 --> 00:01:58.144
11 to 16.

00:01:59.392 --> 00:02:03.296
A becker for every man, that is half a shekel,

00:02:03.264 --> 00:02:05.536
After the shekel of the sanctuary,

00:02:05.440 --> 00:02:08.000
For everyone that went to be numbered.

00:02:08.064 --> 00:02:10.432
From 20 years old and upward,

00:02:10.528 --> 00:02:15.424
For 603,550 men.

00:02:15.968 --> 00:02:19.200
And of the hundred talents of silver were cast,

00:02:18.944 --> 00:02:21.344
The sockets of the sanctuary.

00:02:21.376 --> 00:02:23.392
And the sockets of the veil.

00:02:23.584 --> 00:02:26.880
And 100 sockets of the 100 talents

00:02:26.880 --> 00:02:29.184
A talent for a socket.

00:02:29.888 --> 00:02:32.352
Exodus chapter 38

00:02:32.384 --> 00:02:35.040
Verses 26 to 27.

00:02:36.800 --> 00:02:41.344
Will you kindly first open your Bibles at Exodus chapter 30?

00:02:41.760 --> 00:02:46.016
For I must commence my discourse by expounding that passage.

00:02:46.624 --> 00:02:54.400
When the account was taken of the number of the children of Israel, the Lord commanded that every male over twenty years of age,

00:02:54.176 --> 00:02:57.472
Should pay half a shekel as redemption money.

00:02:57.600 --> 00:03:00.288
Confessing that he deserved to die.

00:03:00.512 --> 00:03:01.536
Owning.

00:03:01.312 --> 00:03:03.840
that he was in debt to God.

00:03:03.968 --> 00:03:07.040
And bringing the sum demanded as a type.

00:03:06.880 --> 00:03:13.088
Of a great redemption which would by and by be paid for the souls of the sons of men.

00:03:13.664 --> 00:03:15.840
The truth was thus taught,

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:19.104
That God's people are a redeemed people.

00:03:19.360 --> 00:03:22.656
They are elsewhere called the redeemed of the Lord.

00:03:23.328 --> 00:03:26.816
If men reject the redemption which he ordains,

00:03:26.880 --> 00:03:29.216
Then are they not his people?

00:03:29.504 --> 00:03:32.224
For of all his chosen, it may be said.

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:34.688
The Lord hath redeemed Jacob.

00:03:34.560 --> 00:03:38.656
And ransomed him from the hand of him that was stronger than he.

00:03:39.584 --> 00:03:43.616
Whenever we attempt to number up the people of God,

00:03:43.520 --> 00:03:51.808
It is absolutely needful that we count only those who at least profess to have brought the redemption price in their hands.

00:03:51.840 --> 00:03:54.112
And so to have taken part.

00:03:53.888 --> 00:03:56.672
in the atonement of Christ Jesus.

00:03:57.408 --> 00:03:58.496
David

00:03:58.624 --> 00:04:00.512
When he numbered the people,

00:04:00.320 --> 00:04:03.776
did not gather from them the redemption money.

00:04:04.032 --> 00:04:07.328
And hence a plague broke out amongst them.

00:04:07.968 --> 00:04:11.456
He had failed in obedience to the Lord's ordinance.

00:04:11.392 --> 00:04:13.728
And had counted his subjects,

00:04:13.440 --> 00:04:17.536
The artist redeemed people, but merely as so many heads.

00:04:18.304 --> 00:04:22.624
Let us always beware of estimating the number of Christians

00:04:22.432 --> 00:04:26.464
by the number of the population of the countries called Christian.

00:04:27.232 --> 00:04:30.080
For the only true Christians in the world.

00:04:30.176 --> 00:04:34.016
Are those who are redeemed from sin by the blood of the lamb?

00:04:34.112 --> 00:04:36.576
And have personally accepted it.

00:04:36.480 --> 00:04:39.232
The ransom which the Lord has provided.

00:04:39.744 --> 00:04:43.904
Personally brought their redemption money in their hands

00:04:43.808 --> 00:04:46.592
By taking Christ to be theirs.

00:04:46.560 --> 00:04:49.408
And presenting him by an act of faith.

00:04:49.408 --> 00:04:51.008
To the great Father.

00:04:51.936 --> 00:04:52.864
God,

00:04:52.704 --> 00:04:57.184
has upon Earth as many people as believe in Jesus Christ.

00:04:57.216 --> 00:04:59.776
And we dare not count any others.

00:04:59.552 --> 00:05:00.960
To be his.

00:05:00.832 --> 00:05:05.600
But those who can say, in whom we have redemption through his blood,

00:05:05.472 --> 00:05:07.520
The forgiveness of sins

00:05:08.128 --> 00:05:10.240
We must not count heads.

00:05:10.080 --> 00:05:12.224
Which know about Christ?

00:05:12.384 --> 00:05:16.128
But hands which have received the redemption money

00:05:15.968 --> 00:05:18.240
and are presenting it unto God.

00:05:18.688 --> 00:05:22.816
Not so much persons who are called Christians by courtesy.

00:05:23.072 --> 00:05:26.720
As souls that are Christly in very fact,,

00:05:26.976 --> 00:05:29.056
Because they have accepted

00:05:28.768 --> 00:05:30.944
The atoning sacrifice,

00:05:30.880 --> 00:05:34.976
And live before God as redeemed from among men.

00:05:35.648 --> 00:05:37.984
Observe that this redemption

00:05:38.112 --> 00:05:42.880
Without which no one might rightly be numbered among the children of Israel,

00:05:42.784 --> 00:05:45.632
Lest a plague should break out among them.

00:05:46.048 --> 00:05:47.712
Must be personal,

00:05:47.648 --> 00:05:49.152
And individual.

00:05:50.112 --> 00:05:53.824
There was not a lump sum to be paid for the nation.

00:05:53.952 --> 00:05:57.024
Or twelve a-months for the twelve tribes.

00:05:57.344 --> 00:06:01.504
But each man must bring his own half-shekel for himself.

00:06:02.368 --> 00:06:06.688
So there is no redemption that will be of any use to any of you.

00:06:07.040 --> 00:06:12.096
Unless it is personally accepted and brought before God by faith.

00:06:12.928 --> 00:06:14.848
You must each one

00:06:14.848 --> 00:06:18.912
Be able to say for yourself concerning the Lord Jesus,

00:06:18.944 --> 00:06:20.384
He loved me.

00:06:20.256 --> 00:06:22.560
And gave himself for me.

00:06:23.040 --> 00:06:25.984
The doctrine of general redemption,

00:06:25.984 --> 00:06:29.248
Which teaches people to say, "Oh yes,

00:06:29.056 --> 00:06:31.136
We are all sinners, you know.

00:06:30.912 --> 00:06:34.912
Christ died for us, for he has died for us all.

00:06:35.168 --> 00:06:38.592
Lays a very poor foundation for comfort.

00:06:39.488 --> 00:06:44.096
We need not so much a general as a personal redemption.

00:06:43.968 --> 00:06:47.072
A redemption which actually redeems.

00:06:47.264 --> 00:06:50.240
And redeems us as individuals.

00:06:51.200 --> 00:06:54.912
The great sacrifice for the sin of humanity

00:06:54.880 --> 00:06:58.656
Must become to us a personal atonement.

00:06:58.976 --> 00:07:00.544
For only so

00:07:00.448 --> 00:07:03.232
Can we realise its efficacy?

00:07:03.872 --> 00:07:05.024
You must.

00:07:04.800 --> 00:07:08.128
Each one bring Christ unto the Father.

00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:11.808
Taking him into your hands by simple faith.

00:07:12.224 --> 00:07:14.112
No other price

00:07:14.048 --> 00:07:15.456
Must be there.

00:07:15.712 --> 00:07:17.376
But that price

00:07:17.152 --> 00:07:20.192
Must be brought by every individual.

00:07:20.064 --> 00:07:23.744
or else there is no acceptable coming to God.

00:07:24.160 --> 00:07:30.624
It was absolutely essential that each one should bring the half shekel of redemption money.

00:07:31.264 --> 00:07:36.960
For redemption is the only way in which you and I can be accepted of God.

00:07:37.984 --> 00:07:39.232
If birth

00:07:39.424 --> 00:07:40.768
Could have done it?

00:07:41.152 --> 00:07:44.000
They had the privilege beyond all doubt.

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:46.848
For they had Abraham as their father.

00:07:47.552 --> 00:07:52.256
They were linearly descended from the three great patriarchs.

00:07:52.160 --> 00:07:53.824
And they might have said,

00:07:53.728 --> 00:07:56.000
we be Abraham's seed

00:07:55.840 --> 00:07:58.912
And were never in bondage to any man.

00:07:59.232 --> 00:08:00.128
No.

00:08:00.480 --> 00:08:02.976
Salvation is not of blood,

00:08:03.200 --> 00:08:04.736
Nor of birth.

00:08:04.928 --> 00:08:07.072
Nor of the will of the flesh,

00:08:07.264 --> 00:08:09.952
Salvation is by redemption.

00:08:10.304 --> 00:08:13.344
And even the true child of Abraham,

00:08:13.344 --> 00:08:16.608
Must bring his or her redemption money.

00:08:17.184 --> 00:08:18.592
So must you.

00:08:18.912 --> 00:08:21.632
You child of godly parents,

00:08:21.440 --> 00:08:25.984
Find salvation by the redemption which is in Christ Jesus.

00:08:26.144 --> 00:08:27.968
Or be lost for ever.

00:08:28.864 --> 00:08:31.264
Do not believe the falsehood

00:08:31.168 --> 00:08:33.632
Of certain modern divines,

00:08:33.696 --> 00:08:38.432
That you children of godly parents do not need to be converted.

00:08:38.912 --> 00:08:41.344
Because you were born so nobly,

00:08:41.216 --> 00:08:44.576
And brought up so tenderly by your parents.

00:08:44.768 --> 00:08:49.056
You are by nature heirs of wrath, even as others.

00:08:49.344 --> 00:08:51.744
You must be born again.

00:08:51.840 --> 00:08:54.592
And you must be personally redeemed.

00:08:55.040 --> 00:08:57.312
As well as unbelieving children.

00:08:57.600 --> 00:09:00.064
Or else you will perish.

00:09:00.320 --> 00:09:06.400
Though the blood of ministers, martyrs and apostles should be running in your veins.

00:09:07.008 --> 00:09:11.488
Redemption is the only ground of acceptance before God.

00:09:11.712 --> 00:09:13.728
A not godly birth.

00:09:13.632 --> 00:09:15.776
Or pious education.

00:09:16.320 --> 00:09:21.888
There were many, no doubt, in the camp of Israel who were men of station and substance.

00:09:21.984 --> 00:09:23.200
But they,

00:09:23.040 --> 00:09:25.376
Must bring the ransom money.

00:09:25.344 --> 00:09:27.648
Or die amid their wealth.

00:09:28.352 --> 00:09:30.688
Others were wise-hearted,

00:09:30.752 --> 00:09:32.960
And skilful in the arts.

00:09:33.472 --> 00:09:36.576
Yet must they be redeemed or die?

00:09:37.184 --> 00:09:38.240
Rank.

00:09:38.272 --> 00:09:40.704
Could not save the princes.

00:09:40.672 --> 00:09:43.584
"Not office, spare the elders."

00:09:43.616 --> 00:09:46.784
Every person of Israel must be redeemed.

00:09:46.976 --> 00:09:48.320
And no one.

00:09:48.160 --> 00:09:50.432
Could pass the muster roll

00:09:50.304 --> 00:09:52.320
Without their half shekel.

00:09:52.544 --> 00:09:54.496
Whatever they might say,

00:09:54.240 --> 00:09:56.064
Or do or be.

00:09:56.736 --> 00:09:58.656
God was their God.

00:09:58.784 --> 00:10:02.880
Because he had redeemed them out of the house of bondage.

00:10:03.040 --> 00:10:04.992
And they were his people.

00:10:05.024 --> 00:10:10.208
because he had put a redemption between his people and the Egyptians.

00:10:10.912 --> 00:10:12.992
Well, did David ask?

00:10:13.344 --> 00:10:18.240
What one nation on earth is like thy people, even like Israel?

00:10:18.304 --> 00:10:22.592
Whom God went to redeem for a people to himself.

00:10:23.520 --> 00:10:24.704
Note well.

00:10:24.576 --> 00:10:26.880
That every Israelite man

00:10:26.784 --> 00:10:29.056
Must be alike redeemed.

00:10:29.504 --> 00:10:33.728
And redeemed with the like, nay, with the same redemption.

00:10:33.856 --> 00:10:36.352
The rich shall not give more,

00:10:36.256 --> 00:10:40.512
And the poor shall not give less than half a shekel.

00:10:41.216 --> 00:10:43.936
Every man requires redemption.

00:10:44.416 --> 00:10:46.688
The one as well as the other.

00:10:47.488 --> 00:10:50.720
Kings on their thrones must be redeemed,

00:10:50.528 --> 00:10:53.280
As well as prisoners in their dungeons.

00:10:53.952 --> 00:10:55.296
The philosopher,

00:10:55.040 --> 00:10:57.856
Must be redeemed as well as the peasant.

00:10:58.784 --> 00:11:00.064
The preacher.

00:11:00.096 --> 00:11:02.304
As much as the profligate,

00:11:02.624 --> 00:11:07.392
And the moralist as certainly as the prostitute or the thief.

00:11:07.904 --> 00:11:10.688
The redemption money for every person

00:11:10.752 --> 00:11:12.512
Must be the same.

00:11:12.416 --> 00:11:14.368
For all have sinned,

00:11:14.240 --> 00:11:16.672
And are in like condemnation.

00:11:18.240 --> 00:11:19.840
And it must be

00:11:19.776 --> 00:11:23.200
A redemption that meets the divine demand

00:11:23.616 --> 00:11:25.120
Because you see

00:11:24.928 --> 00:11:30.816
The Lord not only says that they must each bring half a shekel, no more, no less,

00:11:30.912 --> 00:11:34.560
But it must be the shekel of the sanctuary.

00:11:35.264 --> 00:11:37.568
Not the shekel of commerce.

00:11:37.344 --> 00:11:42.112
Which might be debased in quality or diminished by wear and tear.

00:11:42.688 --> 00:11:44.128
But the coin

00:11:43.872 --> 00:11:48.960
Must be according to the standard shekel laid up in the holy place.

00:11:49.504 --> 00:11:51.136
To make sure of it,

00:11:51.072 --> 00:11:55.296
Moses defines exactly how much a shekel was worth.

00:11:55.456 --> 00:11:57.408
And what its weight was.

00:11:57.440 --> 00:11:58.688
A shekel

00:11:58.656 --> 00:12:00.672
Is twenty geras?

00:12:01.344 --> 00:12:05.824
So you must bring to God the redemption which he has appointed.

00:12:06.016 --> 00:12:07.200
The blood

00:12:07.104 --> 00:12:09.376
And righteousness of Christ.

00:12:09.536 --> 00:12:10.912
Nothing more.

00:12:10.880 --> 00:12:12.480
Nothing less.

00:12:13.024 --> 00:12:15.872
The ransom of Christ is perfection.

00:12:16.384 --> 00:12:17.696
And from it

00:12:17.760 --> 00:12:19.712
There must be no varying.

00:12:20.288 --> 00:12:24.096
The price must satisfy the divine demand.

00:12:24.032 --> 00:12:26.240
And that to the full.

00:12:27.872 --> 00:12:28.864
Note:

00:12:28.736 --> 00:12:32.608
That the price appointed did effectually redeem.

00:12:32.672 --> 00:12:34.976
So far as the type could go.

00:12:35.776 --> 00:12:39.552
Some rejoice in a redemption which does not redeem.

00:12:39.872 --> 00:12:44.640
For the general redemption by which all people are supposed to be redeemed,

00:12:44.512 --> 00:12:47.136
Leaves multitudes in bondage.

00:12:47.328 --> 00:12:51.008
And they go to hell despite this kind of redemption.

00:12:51.584 --> 00:12:52.800
Therefore,

00:12:52.544 --> 00:12:59.328
Do we preach a particular and special redemption of God's own chosen and believing people?

00:13:00.128 --> 00:13:03.616
These are effectually and really ransomed.

00:13:04.032 --> 00:13:07.168
And the precious price once paid for them.

00:13:07.360 --> 00:13:09.184
Has set them free.

00:13:09.824 --> 00:13:13.408
Neither shall any plague of vengeance smite them.

00:13:13.952 --> 00:13:18.848
For the redemption money has procured them eternal deliverance.

00:13:20.032 --> 00:13:23.200
This type is full of instruction.

00:13:23.872 --> 00:13:25.632
The mortgage is studied

00:13:25.728 --> 00:13:27.616
The richer will it appear.

00:13:28.160 --> 00:13:35.712
Every person that is numbered among the children of Israel and permitted to serve God by going out to war,

00:13:35.904 --> 00:13:39.392
Or to take upon him the duties of citizenship,

00:13:39.392 --> 00:13:41.696
Must, as he is numbered.

00:13:41.760 --> 00:13:43.040
Be redeemed.

00:13:43.872 --> 00:13:46.400
So must every one of us.

00:13:46.528 --> 00:13:50.400
If we are truly God's people and God's servants,

00:13:50.432 --> 00:13:53.024
Find our right to be so.

00:13:52.896 --> 00:13:56.864
In the fact of our redemption by Christ Jesus our Lord,

00:13:57.024 --> 00:13:58.112
this.

00:13:57.888 --> 00:14:01.184
Is the joy and glory of each one of us.

00:14:01.504 --> 00:14:03.616
Thou hast redeemed me.

00:14:03.552 --> 00:14:05.760
O Lord God of truth!

00:14:06.016 --> 00:14:12.992
Thank you for listening, friends. This podcast was brought to you by Premier, in association with Spurgeon's College.

00:14:12.960 --> 00:14:16.576
For more Christian podcasts, sermons, and music,

